The President made remarks during a campaign stop at Charlotte Douglas International Airport in North Carolina. He mentioned that the first two stops were cold but had great crowds. He expressed confidence in the electoral performance of his campaign in states like Florida, Ohio, North Carolina, Georgia, and Texas, based on early ballot numbers. When asked about Joe Biden's visit to Ohio, the President stated that he didn't think Biden knew what he was doing. He also addressed reports about declaring victory on Tuesday night, stating that it was a false report and expressing concern about the collection and tabulation of ballots after the election. He criticized the Supreme Court's decision on ballot counting and expressed concern about potential fraud and misuse. The President mentioned his intention to have lawyers involved in the process and expressed concerns about states like Pennsylvania and Nevada. He argued that people should have submitted their ballots earlier and criticized the decision to allow a long period of time for ballot counting after the election.